  "summary": "Important: brotli security update",
  "details": "Brotli is a generic-purpose lossless compression algorithm that compresses data using a combination of a modern variant of the LZ77 algorithm, Huffman coding and 2nd order context modeling, with a compression ratio comparable to the best currently available general-purpose compression methods. It is similar in speed with deflate but offers more dense compression.   \n\nSecurity Fix(es):  \n\n  * Scrapy: python-scrapy: brotli: Python brotli decompression bomb DoS (CVE-2025-6176)\n\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n",
